{"pattern":{"summary":"Fold llvm.fshl(X, 0, Y) into a plain left shift when the second funnel input is all zeros.","match":{"intrinsic":"llvm.fshl","operands":[{"name":"X","kind":"integer or integer vector"},{"name":"Zero","kind":"zero integer or splat-zero vector constant"},{"name":"Y","kind":"integer or integer vector shift amount"}]},"preconditions":[{"condition":"The scalar or vector element bitwidth BW is a power of 2."},{"condition":"The operand shapes match the intrinsic signature."}],"rewrite":{"result":"shl X, (Y & (BW - 1))","notes":["This is target-independent.","Masking makes the transform valid for arbitrary Y because fshl shift amounts are modulo BW.","If Y is already provably in [0, BW), the mask may simplify away in later combines, yielding shl X, Y directly.","For vectors, the mask is applied lane-wise as a splat constant of (BW - 1)."]},"semantic_rationale":["For fshl(X, 0, S), the result is (X << (S mod BW)) | (0 >> (BW - (S mod BW))).","The second term is always zero, so the expression reduces to X << (S mod BW).","When BW is a power of 2, (S mod BW) is equivalent to (S & (BW - 1))."],"canonical_examples":["i32: call i32 @llvm.fshl.i32(i32 %x, i32 0, i32 %y) -> shl i32 %x, %y_or_masked","<2 x i16>: call <2 x i16> @llvm.fshl.v2i16(<2 x i16> %x, <2 x i16> zeroinitializer, <2 x i16> %y) -> shl <2 x i16> %x, (%y & <i16 15, i16 15>)"],"implementation_hint":"In InstCombine for llvm.fshl, match operand1 as zero. Query scalar element bitwidth BW; require isPowerOf2_32(BW). Build an and of the shift operand with BW-1 in the appropriate scalar/vector type, then create a shl of operand0 by that masked amount."},"testcases":[{"name":"fshl_i32_zero_rhs_range_arg","ir":"declare i32 @llvm.fshl.i32(i32, i32, i32)

